It's been a day of sorrow but also one of fond remembrance for the family of Kgothatso Mdunana. The 24-year-old engineering student was laid to rest today (Saturday) in Midrand, after her body was repatriated from China last week. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu has the story. JOHANNESBURG - It's been a day of sorrow but also one of fond remembrance for the family of Kgothatso Mdunana. The 24-year-old engineering student was laid to rest on Saturday in Midrand, after her body was repatriated from China last week. WATCH | Kgothatso Mdunana family accepts death as accident She died after falling from a friend's flat on the 13th floor of a building in Hangzhou two months ago. Her mother says the help they got in returning her body home, was a reflection of her daughter's kindness. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports. Watch the video above